choices.text: the Salvadoran Civil War. The Salvadoran Civil War was a civil war in El Salvador fought between the military-led government of El Salvador and the Farabundo Martí National Liberation Front (FMLN) from 1980 to 1992. The war ended with a peace agreement signed in Chapultepec, Mexico City, on January 16, 1992. The war resulted in the deaths of over 75,000 people, the majority of whom were civilians. The war was fought between the military-led government of El Salvador and the Farabundo Martí National Liberation Front (FMLN), a coalition of five leftist rebel groups.
